ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

This project focuses on predicting hair fall risk using machine learning techniques based on lifestyle, health, and personal factors.
The system classifies individuals into Low Risk or High Risk categories and also performs user segmentation using clustering.

The project includes:

Data preprocessing and cleaning

Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

Supervised machine learning models

Model evaluation using multiple metrics

Clustering for user segmentation

Risk scoring visualization

ğŸ¯ Objectives

Identify key factors contributing to hair fall

Build and compare multiple ML classification models

Predict hair fall risk (Low / High)

Segment users using clustering techniques

Visualize correlations, performance metrics, and risk scores

